        <p>No-shows are the silent profit killer for driving schools. Good scheduling software provides tools to dramatically reduce them.</p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Automated Reminder Strategy</h3>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg my-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">The most effective reminder sequence:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><strong>24 hours before:</strong> Detailed reminder with time, instructor, pickup location, and what to bring.</li>
            <li><strong>2 hours before:</strong> Brief confirmation reminder. Last chance to reschedule.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm"><strong>SMS is essential:</strong> 98% open rate compared to 20% for email. Most people read texts within minutes.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Easy Rescheduling Options</h3>

        <p>Often, students who no-show intended to reschedule but found it too difficult. Make rescheduling effortless:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>Include reschedule links directly in reminder messages</li>
          <li>Allow rescheduling through the student portal without calling</li>
          <li>Set a reasonable rescheduling deadline (e.g., 12-24 hours before)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Related: <a href="/blog/reduce-no-shows-driving-school/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">How to Reduce No-Shows at Your Driving School</a></p>

