          <li><strong>Update availability:</strong> Mark themselves unavailable for specific times</li>
          <li><strong>Access student information:</strong> See student contact info, pickup location, and notes</li>
          <li><strong>Record lesson notes:</strong> Log what was covered and student progress</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="evaluation" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">How to Evaluate Scheduling Software</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Must-Test During Trial</h3>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Calendar usability:</strong> Spend 15 minutes scheduling, rescheduling, and cancelling. Is it intuitive?</li>
          <li><strong>Student experience:</strong> Check the student portal. Can students see their lessons and progress easily?</li>
          <li><strong>Mobile experience:</strong> Test both admin calendar and student booking on your phone.</li>
          <li><strong>Conflict prevention:</strong> Try to create a double-booking. The system should prevent it completely.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Red Flags</h3>

